AGI -&nbsp;Tuscany is confirmed as a preferred location by foreigners who choose Italy for the fateful "yes". It is here, in fact, that in 2023 the greatest number of marriage was celebrated, compared to the other regions: 2600 international marriages, 12.5% more than 2022>, for a turnover of 29.5%, up to 170 million euros, for an average expenditure of 65 thousand euros, that is 15.3% more than 2022. The numbers emerge from the update of the Destination Weddings in Tuscany Observatory carried out by the Tourist Office for Tuscany Tourist Promotion and certify the success of the three-year call with which Tuscany for Weddings, division of Destination Florence Convention &amp; Visitors Bureau for the promotion of the wedding offer of Tuscany, has operated on behalf of the regional agency. A collaboration that today renews with the signature of a protocol of understanding between the two entities, which further expands the agreement between Destination Florence CVB and TPT: in addition to the wedding, the new protocol, deliberated by the allotted to Tourism of the Tuscany Region, previews a work in tandem on the congress tourism.
&nbsp;
"The number of foreign citizens electing Tuscany as a destination to celebrate the wedding - comments the president of the Tuscany Region, Eugenio Giani -, a result that fills us with satisfaction. The decision, matured a few years ago, to create an ad hoc project, Tuscany for Weddings, > thank you to the collaboration between Tuscany Tourist Promotion and Destination Florence Convention &amp; Visitors Bureau to promote the wedding offer, turned out to be winning. I believe that for the development of this tourist segment Tuscany has everything you need: authentic places in breathtaking scenery combined with an impeccable organization".
&nbsp;
&nbsp;"For several years - adds the Councillor to economy and tourism Leonardo Marras - Tuscany is among the most chosen destinations by foreign citizens to celebrate their wedding. The 'most beautiful day' is an emotion to live, but at the same time an event to be treated in every detail involving many professionals. The work carried out in these years with Tuscany Tourist Promotion and Destination Florence Convention &amp; Visitors Bureau with the project Tuscany for Weddings, and which today expands also to the congress tourism, is therefore a strength on which to continue to point. The constant increase of those who choose this region to join in marriage is the confirmation of the goodness of this collaboration".
&nbsp;
"The excellent data on the wedding segment go hand in hand with the need to value the congress tourism sector - adds the Director of Tuscany Tourist Promotion, Francesco Tapinassi. - from here comes a protocol of understanding that confirms and expands the relationship between Tuscany Tourist Promotion and the Destination Florence Convention &amp; Visitors Bureau, engaged on both segments wedding and MICE. Moreover, the role of Destination Florence CVB in the organization of the Grand Dèpart del Tour de France from Florence to June: an additional element of connection between the Bureau's action and our agency, considering the commitment of TPT in the valorization of the cycling sector".
&nbsp;
"The data on the wedding of our region certify the goodness of the work done in recent years - explains Jacopo Vicini, president of Destination Florence Convention &amp; Visitors Bureau. - already in 2015, we were the first Convention Bureau to create a division dedicated to the wedding segment, in order to promote in an organic, coherent and structured way the offer of Tuscany in Italy and abroad, and the constant increase of presences demonstrates our foresight and rewards our efforts".
&nbsp;
Beyond pandemic - The data demonstrates the overcoming of the pandemic period. To choose Tuscany to marry are mainly couples from the United States and the United Kingdom > (60%), while with regard to the type of celebration, the symbolic rite is still the preferred one (66.3%), > with the civil and religious one that stands at 22.4% and 11.3% respectively. 9.3% of civil and symbolic rites also concern civilian unions celebrated among people of the same sex.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;Almost a couple out of two, i.e. 48.2% of the total, was entrusted to a wedding planner to crown their dream of love (+5% compared to 2022), while regarding the chosen period 89% of the celebrations took place between April and September.
&nbsp;
Overnight and invited» - Although the average duration of the stay of guests decreased slightly (3,2 nights compared to 3,3 of 2022), the overnight stays in the accommodation facilities rose to 496 thousand (+14.5%) and the total business volume reached 168.7 million euros (+29.5%). The average number of guests increased (60.6 versus 56 in 2022) and the number of guests between 51 and 100 increased by 25%, representing 63% of the total. Overall arrivals grew by 21.7%, attesting to 157 thousand, while tourist attendance linked to the wedding celebrations of foreign couples was 496 thousand (+14.5%).
&nbsp;
The preferred locations are villas, from 22% of 2022 to 26.7% of 2023, followed by historical residences (17.5%) and farms (15%). Castles (11.7%), villages (10%), luxury hotels (7.5%) resorts (5%) and others (hotels, restaurants, bathing establishments, private houses). The expectations for 2024 - Even for 2024 the expectations of the sector are of further growth of the market, with an estimated increase around 9.1%. The main arrivals will still remain the extra EU, > but will consolidate the demand from Scandinavian, German, Swiss, Dutch, Austrian, Spanish and French couples.
&nbsp;
Italian couples - In 2023, 630 Italian couples came to the supply chain companies, coming from other regions, who chose Tuscany for the fateful "yes", generating a total turnover of 25 million euros. As for the average number of guests, in 2023 it stood at 89.9, against 78.7 of 2022, while the average expenditure for the organization of the event amounted to 40 thousand euros (39.700 euros, +19% compared to 2022).
&nbsp;
Overall arrivals from outside the region were 56,600, while tourist attendance 98,300. An alliance for the wedding in Tuscany - The positive picture emerged certifies the success of Tuscany for Weddings, division of Destination Florence Convention &amp; Visitors Bureau dedicated to promoting the Tuscan territory towards the international wedding market. An alliance that today strengthens thanks to the signature of a protocol between the two realities, which extends the collaboration not only to the wedding sector, but also to the MICE (Meeting, Incentive, Conference, Exhibition) in order to realize activities that can enrich the entire territory intercepting a quality tourism. &nbsp;

