AGI - A Flixbus coach crashed in the night in A1 near Modena and in the impact a 19-year-old Congolese passenger died and six other people were injured, of which one in a serious way is in private prognosis. Around 2, at km 174 southward, for reasons still to be ascertained the driver would have lost control of the bus that hit the barrier 'New Jersey' on the right side of the road, without involving other means. The motorway between Modena Sud and Valsamoggia on the lane towards Naples has long been closed.
&nbsp;
Flixbus left Milan and was headed to Rome. On the spot the road police of Bologna Sud intervened along with the rescuers of 118, with four ambulances, an automedical and elixoccorso. Vignola's firefighters freed some people left framed. The most severe wounded is a 58-year-old, native to the province of Frosinone, admitted in Reanimation at the hospital Maggiore of Bologna, with reserved prognosis.
